        'code' => 'Data Subjects (Control 14)',
        'title' => 'Data Subject Rights Enablement',
        'description' => 'Data Subjects have certain rights under Law, including the right to access, delete, edit, export, restrict, and object to Processing of their Personal Data (“Data Subject Rights”). When a Data Subject seeks to exercise their rights under Law in respect of their Microsoft Personal Data, the supplier must enable Microsoft to do the following or perform these actions on Microsoft’s behalf:  Assist Microsoft, through appropriate technical and organizational measures, where possible, to fulfill its obligations to respond to requests for Data Subjects seeking to exercise their Data Subject Rights without undue delay. 
 
